  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>shallots</strong></p><p>Mash the <strong>beluga lentils</strong> in a large bowl to form a rough paste</p><p>Add the<strong> diced shallots</strong>, <strong>ground allspice</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cinnamon</strong>, and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Season with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix thoroughly to combine (clean hands is the best way!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turkish-spiced-lentil-pastry-pie-with-herby-bulgur/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of flour</p><p>Unwrap the <strong>puff</strong> <strong>pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a rolling pin and cut into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span></p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> and add the <strong>pastry</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>lentil</strong> <strong>mixture</strong> into 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4]</span> balls and add 1 to the middle of each pastry</p><p>Pull the pastry corners over the lentil balls to form a sealed parcel</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turkish-spiced-lentil-pastry-pie-with-herby-bulgur/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Turn the <strong>pastry parcels</strong> over so that the sealed edges are underneath</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>nigella seeds</strong> (gently press them in with your hands!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25 min or until the pastry is golden and the lentils are warmed through – these are your<strong> Turkish spiced lentil pastry pies</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turkish-spiced-lentil-pastry-pie-with-herby-bulgur/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pies are in the oven, boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turkish-spiced-lentil-pastry-pie-with-herby-bulgur/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate)<strong> half</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[all] </span>the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining garlic for another recipe!</p><p>Combine the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> with the <strong>mayo</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>in a small bowl – this is your<strong> garlic mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turkish-spiced-lentil-pastry-pie-with-herby-bulgur/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> </strong>roughly</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Trim, then slice the<strong> spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Combine the<strong> grated carrot, chopped tomato</strong> and<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a small bowl – this is your<strong> carrot & tomato salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turkish-spiced-lentil-pastry-pie-with-herby-bulgur/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip the<strong> mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Mix the <strong>chopped herbs</strong> through the <strong>cooked bulgur</strong> – this is your<strong> herby bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/turkish-spiced-lentil-pastry-pie-with-herby-bulgur/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Turkish spiced lentil pastry pies</strong> over the <strong>herby bulgur</strong> with the<strong> carrot & tomato salad</strong> and <strong>garlic mayo</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
